>12/29/99</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>2:30:50 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Level limit</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">To have a level limit is good to avoid insane spells. But that will keep us away of some useful skills like double attack and dual weild. <BR>  <BR> We should evaluate the pros and the cons of reaching levels over level 12. <BR>  <BR> Would be great if we can use poison and let the higher level rogues like Bluud and me make it for the guild. Everybody could jump over the enemy with weapon poisoned with diferent poison to give all the effects at the same time. <BR>  <BR> A group of level 17 rogues jumping over other group of players with poison would have really fun results :) <BR>  <BR> Anyway, we have to determine the spells that get each caster type and think about what we could miss by getting on their range. <BR>  <BR> Solorog <BR> Level 38 Rogue on Valon Zek</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#a8a8a8><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Wayman</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>12/30/99</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>4:04:44 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">lvl range</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Keep in mind: If raiding misty thicket, you will encounter TONS of druids there. Their lv 14 dot is pretty good, but not nearly as rough as their level 19 stuff (new nuke, I believe). That's right, lv 19, not 20. Level 19 druids can also teleport, so if you are over lv 11, expect some druids to teleport in to attempt to fight you off. <BR>  <BR> Priest spell lvls: 1, 5, 9, 14, 19, 24, 29, 34, etc. <BR>  <BR> Int caster spell lvls: 1, 4, 8, 12, 16, 20, (change here to 5 lv increments) 24, 29, 34, 39, etc.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CCCCCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Wayman</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>12/30/99</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>4:11:59 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Levels</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Personally, I recommend lv 15 as the level cap. Shaman get incredible spells at 14 (compared to what they have before it), and rogues get dw by this level. This avoids the level 24 casters. Unfortunatley, this means that rogues will not have da. </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#a8a8a8><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Wotan</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>12/30/99</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>5:16:01 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Level 11 is the ticket</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">What the man said about druids.  Wouldnt hurt to have a few higher to watch our backs...but they will be at risk.   <BR>  <BR> I'm gonna try to have sow for the festivities. <BR>  <BR> </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CCCCCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Fricka</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>12/30/99</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>6:24:11 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Level limit and druids</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Hi all!  New rogue, Fricka here: <BR>  <BR> Some notes on the druids.  They do get a variety of self teleport spells at level 19 but the nearest level 19 druid ring is in East Commons, not in Misty Thicket itself, so that would give us a little time to &quot;hit and run&quot; as Wotan says.  Course, those that live in Misty may be a problem but since a Druid can bind anywhere they probably wont bind in Misty unless they are already fighting there. <BR>  <BR> Wotan:  Go for the sow!  By the way...look I'm posting!</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#a8a8a8><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/btheshanks.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=blye>Blye</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Local user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>1/2/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>7:38:34 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Level limit and druids</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">In a previous post, I recommended that we stay below level 12 to avoid the casters with the level 20 spells.  After reading this information it is obvious we need to stay below level 11..  This is going to be for our first raid into the Thickett.  Go Shanks!!!</font><P>Leader of the Shanks, until I get killed or you find somebody better...<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CCCCCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Wotan</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>1/3/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>10:23:40 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The important thing</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">is that we keep the band leveling together.  So for the first raid we should stick to the lvl 10 limit.  One or two higher members to pitch in couldn't hurt, but they will be vulnerable and we will be unable to succor them if they meet resistance.   <BR>  <BR> Another thing we ought to think about, while we are still relatively unknown, is a private means to communicate the important intelligence, such as dates, level limits, and strategies for upcoming raids.   <BR>  <BR> I'm thinking something like the Root Cellar with strict controls on membership... <BR>  <BR> Wotan</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#a8a8a8><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uvladmirttf.showPublicProfile>Vladmir TTF</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.angelfire.com/on2/ttf/ttficon.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>1/7/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>7:02:57 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/on2/ttf/images/vlad.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Go to the private discussion</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I think that would be fine place to discuss the actual attack times and strategies. <BR>  <BR> You should have the password via email.</font><P>-Vladmir Ebonglade-<br>
